26/05/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Thousands gathered in the centre of Athens and in other cities on Wednesday (May 25th) to protest austerity measures launched by the government.
The rallies, inspired by recent turmoil in Spain, were organised via Facebook.
According to local media, over 10,000 people joined the protest in Athens' central square.
The rally in Thessaloniki attracted around 5,000 participants.
Similar protests were organised in other cities.
(SKAI, Ta Nea, To Vima - 25/05/11)
